<component type="desktop-application">
  <id>com.anthropic.ClaudeDesktop</id>
  <name>Claude</name>
  <summary>Desktop app for Claude</summary>
  <metadata_license>CC0-1.0</metadata_license>
  <project_license>LicenseRef-proprietary=https://claude.ai/legal/consumer-terms</project_license>
  <developer id="com.anthropic">
    <name>Anthropic</name>
  </developer>
  <url type="homepage">https://claude.ai</url>
  <url type="help">https://support.claude.com/</url>
  <url type="vcs-browser">https://code.claude.com/docs/en/desktop-linux</url>
  <description>
    <p>This is a community package of Claude Desktop, maintained independently and unaffiliated with Anthropic. It repackages Anthropic's official Linux Debian package unmodified.</p>
    <p>Claude Desktop provides the Claude chat experience together with desktop integrations for coding workflows on supported Linux systems.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Chat with Claude from a native desktop window.</li>
      <li>Use Claude coding workflows from the Desktop experience.</li>
      <li>Review changes, terminal output and previews in one app.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Permissions: this package grants network, display, GPU, audio, notifications and keyring access for the core desktop app. It does not grant broad home-directory or host-device access by default; Code project access and Cowork's KVM/QEMU-based environment may require additional user-granted overrides and are not yet verified in this Flatpak package.</p>
  </description>
  <content_rating type="oars-1.1"/>
  <categories>
    <category>Development</category>
    <category>Office</category>
    <category>Utility</category>
  </categories>
